About the 14 karat gold :

The fineness of a precious metal object represents the weight of fine metal therein, in proportion to the total weight which includes alloying base metals and any impurities. Alloy metals are added to increase hardness and durability of jewelry, alter colors.

Karats measure the parts per 24, so that 18 karat = 18⁄24 = 75%

(14 karat = 14 carat / 14 k /14 kt / 14 ct )
